{
  "batch": "Architecture & Coupling",
  "batch_index": 1,
  "assessments": {
    "cross_module_architecture": 78.0
  },
  "dimension_notes": {
    "cross_module_architecture": {
      "evidence": [
        "Contract/action identity is re-exported in multiple packages (`protocol/actionids`, `protocol/contracts/protocolfamily`, and `uploadsvc/contractspec`) instead of being consumed via one narrow boundary, creating multiple import entry points for the same domain constants.",
        "Both `goseg/protocol/contracts/protocolfamily/specs.go` and `goseg/uploadsvc/contractspec/specs.go` publish compatibility-style alias constants (including root/namespace/action IDs), which blurs ownership of canonical protocol identifiers.",
        "`goseg/uploadsvc/actions_test.go` and `goseg/uploadsvc/contractspec/contractspec_test.go` couple upload module tests directly to global protocol catalog internals (`contracts.ActionContractBindings` / `contracts.ActionContractFor`), increasing blast radius of protocol-level changes across module-local tests."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "confidence": "high"
    }
  },
  "findings": [
    {
      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "fragmented_contract_identity_boundary",
      "summary": "Canonical protocol action identity is duplicated across family packages, creating boundary drift risk.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/protocol/actionids/actionids.go",
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/protocolfamily/specs.go",
        "goseg/uploadsvc/contractspec/specs.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`actionids.go` defines canonical namespace/action/contract IDs, but both family spec packages re-export these constants as their own exported symbols.",
        "`protocolfamily/specs.go` and `uploadsvc/contractspec/specs.go` each expose their own contract ID constants (`C2CConnectActionID`, `UploadOpenEndpointActionID`, etc.) that mirror `actionids` values.",
        "This creates multiple authoritative-looking import paths for the same identifiers, so consumers can couple to family packages instead of a single canonical boundary."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Make `protocol/actionids` the only exported source of action identity constants; keep family packages focused on returning `familyspec` declarations and remove public alias constants (or make them unexported/internal if needed for migration).",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "missing_single_contract_identity_boundary"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "compatibility_alias_surface_persists",
      "summary": "Compatibility-style exported aliases in spec packages extend cross-module coupling without adding boundary value.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/protocolfamily/specs.go",
        "goseg/uploadsvc/contractspec/specs.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "Both files export root/namespace/action aliases that are pass-throughs to `actionids` and are not required to build the returned `ActionSpec` slices.",
        "Keeping these aliases public invites downstream imports of spec packages for constants rather than spec declarations, broadening dependency fan-in on packages that should be leaf declaration modules."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Deprecate and remove exported alias constants from spec packages, and document/import canonical IDs from `protocol/actionids` directly to tighten package responsibilities.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "missing_single_contract_identity_boundary"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "upload_tests_tightly_bound_to_global_catalog",
      "summary": "Upload module contract tests are tightly coupled to global protocol registry internals, amplifying change blast radius.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/uploadsvc/actions_test.go",
        "goseg/uploadsvc/contractspec/contractspec_test.go",
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/conformance/fixtures_test.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`actions_test.go` asserts upload behavior by calling `contracts.ActionContractFor`, pulling protocol catalog concerns into upload module tests.",
        "`contractspec_test.go` checks upload expectations against full `contracts.ActionContractBindings` and hard-coded cardinality assumptions.",
        "This makes protocol catalog refactors (even non-behavioral) break upload-local tests, indicating a cross-module test boundary that is too broad."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce a narrow protocol-contract query interface/fixture for upload tests (or module-owned contract snapshot assertions) so upload tests validate module guarantees without depending on full global catalog shape.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "missing_single_contract_identity_boundary"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "Protocol contract identity lacks a single enforced publication boundary, so multiple packages act as quasi-authoritative sources.",
      "Module-level tests use global catalog APIs directly instead of boundary-scoped adapters, increasing cross-module coupling."
    ],
    "likely_symptoms": [
      "compatibility_alias_surface_persists",
      "upload_tests_tightly_bound_to_global_catalog"
    ],
    "possible_false_positives": []
  }
}


